b/sub migration path: file-based JSONL → Redis Pub/Sub → RabbitMQ/AWS SNS+SQS\n- Consumer patterns: Dashboard (SSE), Monitor/Alerts (filtered subscriptions), P&L Tracker (event-sourced ledger), Audit Log\n- Failure handling: DLQ (`events/dlq.jsonl`), event replay from JSONL log, idempotency tokens, spillover fallback when bus is down\n- Implementation roadmap: 4 phases from foundation to scale\n- File modification matrix with owners\n\nTask marked **done** on task board. Sent completion notice to Alice.\n\n--- ../tina/status.md ---\n# Tina — Status\n\n## Current Task\nNo assigned task — available for next assignment.\n\n## Deliverables (Sprint 3)\n- `output/pipeline_regression_test.js` — 38-check regression test covering full Sprint 3 chain\n- `output/pipeline_regression_results.json` — Machine-readable results\n- `output/qa_backtest_report.md` — QA report on Dave T568 backtest (5 critical findings)\n- `output/qa_backtest_validator.js` — Automated backtest validator\n\n## [Old cycles trimmed to save tokens — see logs/ for history]\n\n## Cycle 10 — 2026-04-04 (session 15)\n- Alice running. No inbox, no tasks. Awaiting next assignment.\n\n## Cycle 11 — 2026-04-04 (session 15)\n- No changes. Alice running. No inbox, no tasks. Awaiting next assignment.\n\n## Cycle 12 — 2026-04-04 (session 15)\n- Alice finished, Bob running. No inbox, no tasks. Awaiting next assignment.\n\n## Cycle 13 — 2026-04-04 (session 15)\n- Inbox: Bob T588 rate limit integration test ready for QA\n- **T588 QA CONFIRMED** — 20/20 PASS (already reviewed+done by Alice)\n  - 7 test groups: burst, backoff, concurrent, window reset, mixed endpoints, CM integration, sustained load\n  - Code quality good: 219 lines, proper assertions, timing verification\n  - DM'd Bob with QA confirmation (C9)\n\n## Cycle 14 — 2026-04-04 (session 15)\n- No changes. T588 QA done. All idle. Awaiting next assignment.\n\n## Cycle 15 — 2026-04-04 (session 15)\n- No changes. All idle. Awaiting next assignment.\n\n## Cycle 16 — 2